        public void write(java.lang.Double input)
           throws java.lang.InterruptedException,
                  PeripheralCommunicationException,
                  PeripheralInoperableException
        Description copied from interface: EncoderedMotor
        Sets the motor speed to the new value. This method should be overridden if it is possible to determine when the motor has spun up to its target speed. The input may specify the speed in an implementation-dependent unit, but a given robot platform should implement this so that all motors of the same type will cause the same linear motion after their gearing is considered. This may require instances of this to have fields describing any gearing or other considerations.

        public void writeFast(java.lang.Double input)

        Description copied from interface: EncoderedMotor
        Sets the speed of the motor to the new value. The input may specify the speed in an implementation-dependent unit, but a given robot platform should implement this so that all motors of the same type will cause the same linear motion after their gearing is considered. This may require instances of this to have fields describing any gearing or other considerations. When overridden, a call to super() is required for proper safety control.
